message:
Refresh the extension at `chrome://extensions/` → **↻**, then reload your Claude tab.

**If it still shows 0 sessions**, do this quick diagnostic in Claude's DevTools (F12 → Console):

```javascript
// Paste this in the Claude.ai console to find the actual data-testid values
document.querySelectorAll('[data-testid]').forEach(el => {
  const t = el.getAttribute('data-testid');
  if (t.includes('turn') || t.includes('message') || t.includes('human') || t.includes('ai') || t.includes('user') || t.includes('assistant')) {
    console.log(t, el);
  }
});
```

Paste the output here and I'll add the exact selectors to the adapter in one shot.

Claude.ai requires authentication — I can't inspect it remotely. I need you to run this diagnostic directly in your browser so I can see the exact DOM structure Claude is currently using.

**Step 1 — Open Claude.ai in your active conversation, press F12, go to the Console tab, and paste this:**

```javascript
// Scan all elements with data-testid for anything message/turn related
console.log("=== data-testid values ===");
document.querySelectorAll('[data-testid]').forEach(el => {
  console.log(el.getAttribute('data-testid'), el.tagName, el.className.slice(0,60));
});

// Find the actual message containers
console.log("\n=== Likely message containers ===");
['article','section','[role="row"]','[role="listitem"]','[role="article"]'].forEach(sel => {
  const els = document.querySelectorAll(sel);
  if (els.length) console.log(sel, '->', els.length, 'elements found');
});
```

**Step 2 — Paste the full console output here.**

That output will show me the exact `data-testid` values and element types Claude is using right now, and I'll update the adapter to match precisely in one shot.

Now for Gemini, run this in the Gemini DevTools console (F12 → Console) **while a conversation is open with at least one exchange**:

```javascript
// Paste in Gemini console to find actual content selectors
const uq = document.querySelector('user-query');
const mr = document.querySelector('model-response');
if (uq) {
  console.log('=== user-query structure ===');
  console.log(uq.innerHTML.slice(0, 2000));
}
if (mr) {
  console.log('=== model-response structure ===');
  console.log(mr.innerHTML.slice(0, 2000));
}
```

Paste the output here and I'll patch the Gemini selectors in one shot — same way we fixed Claude.
